A "non-neutral point of view" refers to a perspective or stance that shows bias, partiality, or favoritism toward a particular viewpoint, idea, or group.<br/><br/>This approach emphasizes subjective opinions, personal beliefs, or specific agendas, rather than striving for objectivity or impartiality. In contrast to a neutral point of view, it may advocate for or against certain positions, often leading to unbalanced or one-sided representations.<br/><br/>Consider [[Special:EditPage/{{FULLPAGENAME}}|editing this page]].